1 present and able to monitor the operation of the secure drug take-
2 back bin;
3 (e) Regularly inspect the secure drug take-back bin and the
4 area surrounding the secure drug take-back bin for potential
5 tampering or diversion;
6 (f) Maintain a record of inspections conducted pursuant to
7 paragraph (e) that must:
8 (1) Be documented in writing or electronically and may be
9 combined with records required to be maintained by other state or
10 federal laws or regulations;
11 (2) Include the date and time of each inspection; and
12 (3) Include the initials of the employee who conducted each
13 inspection;
14 (g) Retain each record maintained pursuant to paragraph (f)
15 and any other record relating to the secure drug take-back bin
16 required by state or federal laws or regulations for at least 2 years
17 after the date of the event to which the record pertains; and
18 (h) Notify at least one local law enforcement agency of any
19 suspected or known tampering or theft or significant loss of
20 controlled substances that occurs while the secure drug take-back
21 bin is under the control of the collector not later than 1 business
22 day after the date on which the tampering, theft or significant loss
23 is suspected or discovered.
24 2. A collector shall not receive compensation from a customer
25 of the collector to maintain a secure drug take-back bin or to
26 perform any act required by subsection 1.
27 3. Any collector that maintains a secure drug take-back bin
28 and complies with the provisions of subsections 1 and 2 is not
29 subject to any:
30 (a) Disciplinary action by the Board for any injury or harm
31 that directly results from the collector maintaining a secure drug
32 take-back bin on its premises, unless the injury or harm directly
33 results from the gross negligence or willful and wanton
34 misconduct of the collector; or
35 (b) Restriction established by the governing body of a county,
36 city or other local governmental entity that would affect the
37 collection, transportation, treatment or destruction of the contents
38 of a secure drug take-back bin pursuant to this section.
39 4. Nothing in this section shall be construed to require any
40 entity that:
