6 6. As used in this section:
7 (a) “Collector” means an entity that is:
8 (1) Authorized by and registered with the Drug
9 Enforcement Administration to receive a controlled substance for
10 the purpose of destruction; and
11 (2) In good standing with the Board.
12 (b) “Home-generated pharmaceutical waste” means a
13 pharmaceutical that is no longer wanted or needed by the
14 consumer, including, without limitation, in the form of pills,
15 liquids, inhalers, topical creams, suppositories or patches.
16 (c) “Local law enforcement agency” means:
17 (1) The sheriff’s office of a county;
18 (2) A metropolitan police department; or
19 (3) A police department of an incorporated city.
20 (d) “Maintain” means to own, lease, operate or otherwise host
21 a secure drug take-back bin.
22 (e) “Pharmaceutical” means a drug intended for human or
23 veterinary use, regardless of whether the drug is sold with or
24 without a prescription. The term includes, without limitation,
25 controlled substances listed in schedule II, III, IV or V. The term
26 does not include controlled substances listed in schedule I.
27 (f) “Secure drug take-back bin” means a collection receptacle
28 as described in 21 C.F.R. § 1317.75.
29 (g) “Solid waste management system” has the meaning
30 ascribed to it in NRS 444.500.
